      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Don't worry, most of these leaks are just a simple matter of replacing a small washer, and you won't break anything if you proceed carefully. While you are working, listen for the sound of water rushing or hissing, which would indicate you haven't fully turned off the supply or that water is leaking around the valve, and always keep a towel ready to catch any unexpected drips. If you feel a sudden heavy wrenching resistance while tightening the nut, stop immediately and check if you have stripped the threads or if the washers are still in place. You should also watch for water pooling underneath the sink, as this is your primary sign that the fix isn't complete. If you feel unsure at any point, it is always safer to call a professional plumber than to risk damaging the plumbing.",
